              <li>7:00 PM: Walk through Arts District galleries</li>
              <li>8:00 PM: Drinks at a local bar</li>
              <li><strong>Total:</strong> $30-35 per person + free art viewing</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>The Koreatown Date ($30 per person)</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>7:00 PM: Korean BBQ (cook together at your table)</li>
              <li>8:30 PM: Karaoke or dessert cafe</li>
              <li><strong>Total:</strong> $25-30 per person + entertainment</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section class="content-section">
            <h2>Tips for Maximizing Value</h2>
            
            <h3>1. Research Before You Go</h3>
            <p>
              Check menus online to ensure prices fit your budget. Nothing kills romance like sticker shock when the menu arrives.
            </p>

            <h3>2. Look for Specials</h3>
            <p>
              Many restaurants offer:
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li>Happy hour menus (4-7 PM)</li>
              <li>Prix fixe dinner deals</li>
              <li>Early bird specials</li>
              <li>Weeknight promotions</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>3. Skip Expensive Add-Ons</h3>
            <p>
              Save money by:
            </p>
            <ul>
              <li>Drinking water instead of soda ($3-5 saved)</li>
              <li>Sharing dessert instead of ordering two ($8-12 saved)</li>
              <li>Skipping appetizers if entrees are filling ($12-18 saved)</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>4. Use Credit Card Rewards</h3>
            <p>
              If you have dining rewards cards, use them strategically. Some cards offer 3-4% cash back on restaurants.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="content-section">
            <h2>Budget-Friendly Date Night by Cuisine</h2>
            
            <h3>Mexican & Latin American</h3>
            <p>
              LA has incredible Mexican food at all price points. Authentic taquerias and modern Mexican spots offer amazing food for $20-35 per person.
            </p>

            <h3>Thai & Vietnamese</h3>
            <p>
              Asian cuisines often provide exceptional value. Flavorful, filling meals with great variety for $25-40 per person.
            </p>

            <h3>Pizza & Italian</h3>
            <p>
              Casual Italian spots and pizzerias offer shareable options perfect for date nights. $30-45 per person for quality ingredients and cozy atmospheres.
            </p>

            <h3>Mediterranean & Middle Eastern</h3>
            <p>
              Mezze-style dining with lots of small plates to share. Interactive and affordable at $35-50 per person.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="content-section">
            <h2>The Truth About Budget Dating</h2>
            <p>
              Let's address the elephant in the room: some people worry that budget dates suggest you're cheap or not serious about the relationship. Here's the reality:
            </p>

            <h3>Quality Partners Don't Care About Price</h3>
            <p>
              If someone judges you for choosing an affordable restaurant, they're not the right person. Great partners appreciate thoughtfulness, not expense accounts.
            </p>

            <h3>Experiences Matter More Than Money</h3>
            <p>
              Research shows that couples who do activities together (cooking, exploring, trying new foods) build stronger bonds than those who simply spend money on expensive dates.
            </p>

            <h3>Financial Compatibility is Important</h3>
            <p>
              Dating within your means shows financial responsibility‚Äîan attractive quality in a long-term partner. It also helps you find someone with similar values about money.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="content-section">
            <h2>Final Thoughts</h2>
            <p>
              The best date nights aren't measured by how much you spend, but by the memories you create. Los Angeles offers countless opportunities for romantic, memorable evenings that won't strain your budget. These restaurants prove that you can have excellent food, great ambiance, and meaningful connection without spending a fortune.
            </p>

            <p>
